or 2.2 percent, to 30,193.95 at the 5 p.m. end of trading in
Johannesburg, its lowest closing price since Oct. 28. The
following are among the most active stocks in the South African
market today.    Coal of Africa Ltd. (CZA)  : The coal miner announces
interim results. Shares in the company fell 20 cents, or 2.3
percent, to 8.65 rand.  Efficient Group Ltd. (EFG SJ): The asset-management and
research company may announce six-month results through
February. Efficient traded unchanged at 5.20 rand.    ELB Group Ltd. (ELR)  : The investment trust said net
income climbed to 37.7 million rand ($5.41 million) in the six
months through December from 13 million rand a year earlier. ELB
was steady at 17.75 rand.    Foneworx Holdings Ltd. (FWX)  : The provider of data
services to the security and consumer-goods market said profit
for the six months through December was 9.8 million rand,
compared with 9.7 million rand a year earlier. Foneworx was
unchanged at 1.11 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
